<span id="freeTextContainer7008954502740546559">I really should be giving this 3 stars since it wasn’t by any means perfect and the backstory to the hero was introduced far too late for my liking and there was a lack of Hathaways and I wanted <i>more</i>, but I still enjoyed this so bloody much! I devoured it, though my feelings whilst reading the story would fluctuate between disinterest (because the character/their relationship was so closed off) and warmth.<br/><br/>Let’s settle on 3.5 🌟. <br/><br/>I’m still enjoying the heck out of this series. </span>

